  "gitCommitMessage": "Unified model cache + Kokoro bundled-asset path\n\nAdds src/runtime/model-cache.ts as the single registry for all downloaded\nmodel artifacts. Each entry has a manifest (URL, filename, expected/minimum\nsize); ensureModel(id) is idempotent — returns cached path on hit, downloads\non miss. Cache lives at documentDirectory/wave-models/<id>/. Pulls\nLiteRT 4.7 GB out of the wrapper's hidden Library/Caches/litert_models/\ndir into the unified location so the cache panel can see it.\n\nTest pages rewired:\n  - LiteRT smoke now calls ensureModel('litert-wave'), then passes the local\n    path to wrapper.loadModel() (bypassing the wrapper's auto-download).\n  - Whisper smoke calls ensureModel('whisper-tiny-en') instead of doing its\n    own FileSystem.createDownloadResumable.\n  - Both surface unified progress + error semantics.\n\nCache panel (src/screens/CachePanel.tsx) embedded at the bottom of the\ndev menu home screen. Shows each model with cached/missing badge, on-disk\nsize vs expected, and per-row Download / Re-download / Clear buttons plus\na \"Clear all caches\" footer. Polls inspectCache() after every action.\n\nKokoro switched to bundled-asset path 2:\n  - scripts/download-kokoro.sh fetches sherpa-onnx/releases/.../kokoro-en-\n    v0.19.tar.bz2 (~330 MB) and unpacks into mobile/assets/kokoro/.\n  - mobile/.gitignore excludes /assets/kokoro/ (and /assets/whisper-coreml/\n    for the same pattern when we add CoreML).\n  - KokoroTestScreen.tsx now loads via sherpa-onnx createTTS({ modelPath:\n    { type: 'asset', path: 'kokoro' } }) and routes missing-file errors to a\n    \"run scripts/download-kokoro.sh\" guidance panel.\n  - sherpa-onnx's TTS surface is under react-native-sherpa-onnx/tts per the\n    package's exports map; root re-export is limited.\n\nPolish item documented in model-cache.ts: documentDirectory is iCloud-\nbacked; for a 4.7 GB LiteRT bundle that's wasteful. Move to\nLibrary/Application Support/ or set NSURLIsExcludedFromBackupKey when the\nexpo-file-system version we're on exposes the flag.\n\nType-check: tsc --noEmit exits 0.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
